<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870831-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Fourth FinancialAgrees to AcquireUnion Financial Corp.</HL><DD> 08/31/87</DD><SO>  </SO><IN> FRTHTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WICHITA, Kan.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Fourth Financial Corp. said it agreed to acquire Union Financial Corp., a one-bank holding company, in a stock swap it valued at $18.8 million.    Fourth Financial, a bank holding company, said Union Financial owns the largest bank in Manhattan, Kan., Union National Bank andamp; Trust Co., with $158 million in assets and 53% of the city's commercial bank deposits.    To complete the swap, Fourth Financial said each share of Union Financial common would be converted into about 31 common shares of Fourth Financial. In national over-the-counter trading Friday, Fourth Financial closed at $22.75, down 25 cents.    The acquisition is subject to definitive agreement, and to regulator and shareholder approval. </TEXT></DOC>